  <h4><i>Frequently Asked Questions:</i></h4>
  <a href="#" class="question">
1.	How do I prevent my products from being sold to out of country mailing addresses?
  <br />
  </a>
  <div class="answer" style="display:none;">
    <p>
  On your merchant dashboard, under “My Profile”, you can list the regions to which you are willing to ship your product. A customer who’s shipping address is in any of the regions not selected by you will be prevented from purchasing that product.
    </p>
  </div>

  <a href="#" class="question">
2.	How often do I get paid?
<br />
  </a>
  <div class="answer" style="display:none;">
    <p>
By default, you will be paid daily for the transactions that occurred 7 days previously. In the near future, this will be adjustable to suit your needs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <a href="#" class="question">
3.	How do I get paid?
<br />
  </a>
  <div class="answer" style="display:none;">
    <p>
  On your dashboard, you will see a link labelled "My Account". If you follow this link, you will see a form requesting your bank details.
  Completing this form permits our payments provider, Stripe, the ability to make direct deposits into your bank account.
  Completing this banking form is necessary in order to get paid.
    </p>
    <p>
    Since we permit you to sell in both CAD and USD currencies, we also allow you to connect both a USD and a CAD bank account.
    Funds from any orders placed in USD will be deposited into your USD account, and likewise for any orders received in CAD.
    </p>
    <p>
    If you only have either a CAD bank account or a USD bank account, Stripe will exchange your funds into the currency of your bank at the time of transfer at current exchange rates.
    </p>
  </div>

  <a href="#" class="question">
4.	How do I upload products to my Ski-Lines store?
<br />
  </a>
  <div class="answer" style="display:none;">
    <p>
One of our main goals is to make adding products and managing inventory as easy as possible.
On your dashboard, you will see a button labelled “Add New Product”. Once you click this button, you will be shown a form requesting all the information related to a single product.

  </p>
  <p>
Also on your dashboard, you will see another button labelled "Upload CSV File". If you follow this link, you will be shown instructions for how to add products listed in a file with a .csv extension. You can easily export an Excel file to a .csv file from within your Excel file.
Once you have completed the bulk upload, you will then have add photos, inventory, and any other peices of information required to start selling those products.
    </p>
  </div>

  <a href="#" class="question">
5.	How do I charge for shipping?
<br />
  </a>
  <div class="answer" style="display:none;">
    <p>
The evidence is quite clear that the checkout experience is significantly improved the sooner the customer knows exactly how much they will be charged.
As such, we have committed to a simple, one size fits all shipping charge system. Meaning, you set a flat fee for shipping for each product, which will be applied to all customers across the board, regardless of where they live in your country.
If the customer lives outside of your country, you can set a different fee for international shipments. You may also set both these prices in CAD and USD.
  </p>
  <p>
All in all, you have to make an educated estimation as to what your average shipping cost will be fore each product, and set that as the shipping fee.
If you are selling in both currencies, you will have 4 shipping prices to enter: domestic shipping charges in both CAD and USD, and international shipping charges in both CAD and USD.
    </p>
  </div>

  <a href="#" class="question">
6.	Can I sell my summer products, such as running or cycling gear?
<br />
  </a>
  <div class="answer" style="display:none;">
    <p>
We don’t just operate ski-lines.com. We also own the rights to bike-lines.com, run-lines.com, swim-lines.com, and product-lines.com, which will be launching in spring of 2017. In the meantime, we suggest that you focus on your skiing equipment, but anticipate having a very similar solution, accessible through a single platform, for your summer products come the spring.
    </p>
  </div>

  <a href="#" class="question">
7.	What information do you need for us to start selling?
<br />
  </a>
  <div class="answer" style="display:none;">
    <p>
All we need for you to begin is for you to accept our terms and conditions.
However, in order to permit transfers to your bank account, there is a certain amount of information required to verify your identity.
This information is requested in the “My Account” page in your dashboard.
This is not only a legal requirement, but also makes complete practical sense for us to mitigate against the potential for fraud.
Furthermore, as your account becomes increasingly active, and you start to process large volumes of transactions, greater measures for identity verification are required.
As such, there is a multi-step process for identity verification. We do this in order to permit you to start selling as fast as possible.
<br /><br />
</p>
<p><b>Step 1—To start selling:</b></p>
<p>
The only actions required by you to start selling is to accept the terms and conditions on your account, add products, list the inventory available, and mark your products as “Active”.
<br /><br />
</p>
<p><b>Step 2—To receive bank transfers:</b></p>
<p>
To receive bank transfers, you must update your account with some identifying pieces of information: merchant Business Number, account representative’s last four digits of social security number, social insurance number, and, of course, your bank account details. What we ask for really depends on the state of verification. Once you submit this information, it will not subsequently be available for display. In most cases, this is sufficient to fully verify your account.
<br /><br />
</p>
<p><b>Step 3—Not yet verified, and selling more than $20,000:</b></p>
<p>
In rare cases, we may require the account representative to upload a photocopy of a piece of government issued identification.

No sensitive data is stored on our servers, or even on the Ski-Lines site. Once this information is submitted, you will no longer see these form fields.
    </p>
  </div>

