  <a href="#" class="question">
11.	What if a customer wants a refund or a return?
<br />
  </a>
  <div class="answer" style="display:none;">
    <p>
The customer is to contact the store the product was purchased from, and, if exchanging an item, coordinate the exchange directly with them. If the customer wants to do a straight return, the customer, again, contacts the store directly to coordinate the shipping for a return.
The merchant then follows the link in the specific order to which the return is related to complete a refund for the customer. The customer will be refunded the product and the tax paid on the product, but not the shipping or any tax paid on the shipping by default, but the merchant can customize this on the returns form.
    </p>
  </div>

  <a href="#" class="question">
12.	How is sales tax calculated?
<br />
  </a>
  <div class="answer" style="display:none;">
    <p>
Calculating sales tax can be incredibly tricky when dealing with three different levels of sales tax in the U.S., and the harmonized sales tax in Canada.
In addition, there is no standard formula accross the board for deciding whether it is the customer or the retailer's sales tax rates that apply.
As such, we use TaxJar to do all the heavy lisfting of these various sales tax calculations.
It is their primary focus to stay on top of any changes in local sales tax rates or policies, which allows us to stay focused on providing an exceptional marketplace.
    </p>
  </div>

    <a href="#" class="question">
13.	Who pays for shipping in a return?
<br />
    </a>
    <div class="answer" style="display:none;">
      <p>
The customer is responsible for any shipping fee and taxes payable for returning items as a default, but this is customizable by you when submitting a request for a return.
      </p>
    </div>

    <a href="#" class="question">
14.	Can I set my own return policy?
<br />
    </a>
    <div class="answer" style="display:none;">
      <p>
Yes, merchants can set their own return policy as a default for their account, and then edit the policy on a per product basis.
      </p>
    </div>

    <a href="#" class="question">
15.	How are products ranked for display on the website?
<br />
    </a>
    <div class="answer" style="display:none;">
      <p>
Products are displayed based on the user’s location. For example, if a user visits Ski-Lines.com/shop on their device in Winnipeg, they will first see all the products for sale by retail stores located in Winnipeg. If a user searches for a specific product, the results will be listed first by relevance, and then distance from their current location.
      </p>
